Best Products Inc said sales forthe four weeks ended February 28 were off 12.7 pct to 111.3 mlndlrs from 127.6 mln dlrs a year before, excluding sales fromcatalog stores and Ashby's Ltd outlets that were closed or soldlast year.    The company said in an effort to improve gross margins, itsignificantly cut promotional activity in February from a yearearlier.  In addition, it said it distributed its springcatalog nationwide in February last year and will distribute itin March this year. Reuter&#3;